sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant UI as Open WebUI
    participant API as FastAPI Orchestrator
    participant CONV as Conversation Service
    participant G as Qwen3Guard
    participant EMB as Embedding Service
    participant SP as Sparse Encoder
    participant Q as Qdrant
    participant R as Reranker
    participant T as Tavily Web Search
    participant LLM as Qwen3.5-4B (Remote)
    participant LS as LangSmith

    Note over U,LS: Backend owns conversation state, retrieval inputs, citation rendering, transport shaping, and trace output

    U->>UI: Send chat request
    UI->>API: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(request.messages, stream: true/false)
    API->>CONV: normalize_messages + classify_task + summarize/rewrite
    CONV-->>API: raw_query + resolved_query + conversation_context + task_type

    alt Auxiliary task (title / tags / follow_ups)
        API->>LLM: Backend-owned auxiliary prompt
        LLM-->>API: Task output
        API->>LS: trace root output<br/>answer + citations + task_type + resolved_query
        API-->>UI: OpenAI-shaped response
    else Chat task
        Note over G,R: Guard, embedding, and reranker log latency + memory_allocated / memory_reserved / max_memory_allocated per request

        API->>G: POST /classify<br/>(role: "input", text: resolved_query)
        G-->>API: safe / unsafe + metadata

        alt Input unsafe
            API->>LS: trace root output<br/>apology answer only
            API-->>UI: Safe denial
        else Input safe
            API->>EMB: POST /embed<br/>(resolved_query, is_query=true)
            EMB-->>API: Dense query vector
            API->>SP: underthesea tokenization + BM25 query embedding

            alt Sparse encoder ready
                SP-->>API: Sparse query vector
                API->>Q: hybrid_search(dense, sparse)
            else Sparse encoder error
                SP-->>API: error
                API->>Q: hybrid_search(dense, None)
            end

            Q-->>API: Retrieved chunks
            API->>R: POST /rerank<br/>(resolved_query + passages)
            R-->>API: Top reranked chunks

            opt Web fallback triggered
                API->>T: search(resolved_query)
                T-->>API: Web results with source_type="web"
            end

            Note over API: Build final_context + citation_pool keyed by stable context_id

            alt No usable context
                API->>LS: trace root output<br/>no-context answer
                API-->>UI: "Không tìm thấy thông tin liên quan"
            else Context available
                API->>LLM: Generate with conversation_context + raw_query<br/>and source metadata / [[cite:context_id]] instructions
                LLM-->>API: Draft answer

                API->>G: POST /classify<br/>(role: "output", prompt: resolved_query)
                G-->>API: safe / unsafe + metadata

                alt Output unsafe on first pass
                    API->>LLM: Retry once with safety feedback
                    LLM-->>API: Retry answer
                    API->>G: Re-check output safety
                    G-->>API: safe / unsafe
                end

                opt No valid citation placeholders
                    API->>LLM: Repair pass that only adds [[cite:context_id]]
                    LLM-->>API: Repaired answer
                end

                Note over API: Render inline citations as [title](url)<br/>or title (source) when URL is missing
                API->>LS: trace root output<br/>answer + citations + task_type + resolved_query

                alt stream = false
                    API-->>UI: choices[0].message.content = answer
                else stream = true
                    API-->>UI: SSE delta.content chunks sliced from answer<br/>without whitespace normalization or trailing source block
                end

                UI-->>U: Answer with inline citations
            end
        end
    end
